      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DIVOT (1) is worth forgiving for his last effort when eighth (31.02) at Cannington over 520m. Form here at the trip excellent including six wins. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Worth another chance. TARAWI LOCK (5) is generally an honest type in the frame at 13 of 37 starts but missed the placings last time when fifth (25.31) over 440m at Goulburn. Solid record at this trip including 11 wins. Meets a moderate line up and should run well. INCREDIBLE HEART (2) has been a little hard to follow, missing the frame last time but was a Grade 5 winner three back and returns to 400m where she tends to run well. Has the ability and looks a key chance here. DANCING DAWN (8) is not to be discarded.",
